  "prompt": "How much percentage of inorganic organic and water present in enamel cementum and dentine?",
  "response": "Dental tissues, including enamel, cementum, and dentine, contain varying proportions of inorganic materials, organic matrix, and water. Here's a breakdown of the typical composition of each:\n\n1. **Enamel:**\n   - **Inorganic Material:** Approximately 96%\n   - **Organic Material:** About 1-2%\n   - **Water:** Around 2-3%\n\n2. **Dentine:**\n   - **Inorganic Material:** Approximately 70%\n   - **Organic Material:** About 20%\n   - **Water:** Around 10%\n\n3. **Cementum:**\n   - **Inorganic Material:** Approximately 45-50%\n   - **Organic Material:** About 20-25%\n   - **Water:** Around 25-30%\n\nThese figures can vary slightly depending on factors such as age and the general health of the teeth. However, these percentages provide a general understanding of the composition of these dental tissues.",
